Want to verify your vacation carryover?  Beginning January 22, 2001, all=20
eligible Enron employees will be able to access the hours of vacation that=20
were carried over from the previous year by going to the eHRonline website.

1. Navigate to the eHRonline website:  http://ehronline.enron.com.
2. Read the disclaimer; click Accept.
3. Enter your User ID and Password; click Logon.
4. Select Time Management from the menu at the left.
5. Select Vacation Information from the drop-down menu.

To see all types of vacation (accrual, lump sum, vacation), click the radio=20
button for "All types."
Click Display.

To see specific types of vacation (accrual, lump sum, vacation), click the=20
radio button below "All types" and make your selection from the drop-down=20
menu.

Click Display.

Click Exit to log off.

The system will default to show all types of vacation, including (if=20
available) Vacation-(Accrual) or Vacation-(Lump Sum) or Vacation.  The=20
carryover amount will be displayed next to the Type: "Vacation" under the=20
"Entitlement" column.

Enron policy states that employees are entitled to a maximum of 40 hours of=20
vacation carryover without supervisor approval.  Hours in excess of 40 hours=
=20
are subject to supervisor approval and will be updated once supervisor=20
approval has been received

If you have questions regarding your vacation, please call the payroll=20
hotline at 713.345.5555.

